                                        <h3 style="color:black">2. Hemkund Sahib </h3>

                                        <p>Uttarakhand is considered to be one of the most sacred places in India. If you are preparing an India tourism itinerary, do not forget to mention the Hemkund Sahib gurudwara. People from across the country pay visit to Hemkund Sahib, meditate, worship, and sing prayers to pay respect to God. Hemkund Sahib is a famous place that calls a million of people, especially Sikhs every year. This sacred land has a vast and engaging history. Also known as Hemkunt Sahib, the place is located in Chamoli district of Uttarakhand at 4329 meters above from the sea level and hence demonstrates cold weather in summers as well. Due to low temperature, the kapats of Gurudwara Hemkund Sahib open somewhere in April and close in between October or November. Clearly, you can only plan your yatra in this duration. While you plan a trip, the foremost thing to keep in mind is comfort that makes it easy for you and your family to travel. In most cases, people generally do not pay attention on the comfort level and face a number of issues during the journey. In order to make it perfectly fine for you, we have prepared a number of Hemkund Sahib packages that offer attractive deals and easily fit within your budget. Moreover, our all inclusive India travel packages offer various nearby places in addition to accommodation.</p>

										<p>With us, you can enjoy, explore, and experience the most popular places in India. From the day one to the last day of your trip, we are there to assist you with everything and bring you a desired Hemkund Sahib trip. So, choose the deal that suits you the most and feel on top of the world. In order to gain more information, you can get in touch with us anytime via the provided contact number.</p>
